de.feig.FEDM.Core

Class IInfoGroup

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.feig.FEDM.Core.IInfoGroup

  • public class IInfoGroup
extends java.lang.Object
    Internal class providing Reader info specific methods.
    Description:
    This class realizes the nested interface with special methods for requesting general information for the Reader class ReaderModule.
    Methods of this class can be called with the IInfo member of ReaderModule.

    • Method Detail

      • readReaderInfo

        public IInfoGroup.ReaderInfo readReaderInfo()
                                     throws FeException
        Reads the complete reader information.
        Returns:
        IInfoGroup.ReaderInfo object with all information or, in case of an error, null
        Throws:
        FeException - exception with error code (<0)

        Description:
        Reads the complete reader information and collects these information in a reader info class. (see class description in ReaderInfo)
        This method invokes multiple sendProtocol(0x66) with different modes.

        This method can throw a FedmException, if an error occurs inside the Java Native Interface.

        Description:

        This method invokes multiple sendProtocol(0x6E) with different modes.

        This method can throw a FedmException, if an error occurs inside the Java Native Interface.
